{'contentformat': 'text/x-wiki', 'contentmodel': 'wikitext', '*': '{{PokémonPrevNext/Head|type=Flying|type2=Dragon}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Pokémon|type=Flying|prevnum=713|prev=Avalugg|nextnum=715|next=Noivern|roundleft=tl|roundright=tr}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Disambig|species=Noibat}}\n|}\n{{Pokémon Infobox\n|name=Noibat\n|jname=オンバット\n|tmname=Onbat\n|jtranslit=Onbatto\n|category=Sound Wave\n|typebox=1\n|type1=Flying\n|type2=Dragon\n|abilityn=d\n|ability1=Frisk\n|ability2=Infiltrator\n|abilityd=Telepathy\n|ndex=714\n|karea=Mountain\n|kdex=113\n|height-ftin= 1\'08"\n|height-m=0.5\n|weight-lbs= 17.6\n|weight-kg=8.0\n|egggroupn=1\n|egggroup1=Flying\n|gendercode=127\n|eggcycles=20\n|expyield=49\n|lv100exp=1,000,000\n|color=Purple\n|catchrate=190\n|evtotal=1\n|evsp=1\n|body=09\n|pokefordex=noibat\n|generation=6\n|friendship=70\n}}\n\'\'\'Noibat\'\'\' ([[List of Japanese Pokémon names|Japanese]]: \'\'\'オンバット\'\'\' \'\'Onbat\'\') is a dual-type {{2t|Flying|Dragon}} {{OBP|Pokémon|species}} introduced in [[Generation VI]].\n\nIt [[Evolution|evolves]] into {{p|Noivern}} starting at [[level]] 48.\n\n==Biology==\nNoibat is a pale purple bat-like Pokémon. It has yellow eyes, a black triangular marking on the inner corner of each eye, three tufts of spiked fur on each cheek, two dark purple teardrop-shaped spots on the front of its face, a black lower jaw, and two spiked tufts of fur on its upper lip. Its large, teardrop-shaped ears resemble {{wp|loudspeaker}}s; they are dark purple on the outside with alternating rings of pale and dark purple fading to black on the inside. Fluffy black fur covers its chest and hips. On the middle joint of its wings are small black hands with two fingers and it has two long toes on each foot.\n\nNoibat can be found in pitch black caves. From its large ears, it is capable of emitting ultrasonic waves of up to 200,000 Hertz. It uses these waves to stun large creatures, communicate with other Noibat, and immobilize prey.<ref> [https://web.archive.org/web/20140223190622/http://www.pokemonxy.com/en-us/pokemon/other_pokemon/ Pokémon X and Y site | Other Pokémon (Archived)] </ref> It is also very fond of fruit, and uses its sonar to detect its ripeness.\n\n==In the anime==\n[[File:Ash Noibat.png|thumb|left|250px|Noibat in the {{pkmn|anime}}]]\n[[File:Ash Noibat Egg.png|thumb|left|150px|A Noibat {{pkmn|Egg}} in the {{pkmn|anime}}]]\n===Major appearances===\n====[[Ash\'s Noibat]]====\n{{Ash}}\'s Noibat hatched from an {{pkmn|Egg}} in \'\'[[XY076|A Not-So-Flying Start!]]\'\'. He evolved into a Noivern in \'\'[[XY110|An Electrifying Rage!]]\'\'.\n\n====Other====\nMultiple Noibat debuted in \'\'[[XY033|Calling from Beyond the Aura!]]\'\', where they encountered {{Ash}} and {{ashfr}} after they were agitated by {{TRT}}.\n\nA Noibat appeared in \'\'[[PK26|Pikachu, What\'s This Key?]]\'\'. It was a resident of a world full of ice and snow, which was accessed by {{AP|Pikachu}} and his friends, courtesy of {{p|Klefki}}\'s keys.\n\nFive Noibat appeared in the Hoopa\'s Surprise Ring Adventures short \'\'{{DL|Hoopa\'s Surprise Ring Adventures|In the Dark}}\'\', where they were among the Pokémon rudely awakened by {{an|Hoopa}}\'s summoning of multiple {{p|Litwick}}.\n\n===Minor appearances===\nA Noibat appeared in \'\'[[M17|Diancie and the Cocoon of Destruction]]\'\' as a resident of [[Allearth Forest]].\n{{-}}\n\n===Pokédex entries===\n{{Animedexheader|Kalos}}\n{{Animedexbody|XY033|Noibat|Ash\'s Pokédex|Noibat, the Sound Wave Pokémon. Noibat\'s ears emit ultrasonic waves that can disturb its prey\'s sense of hearing and damage opponents.}}\n{{Animedexbody|XY076|Noibat|Ash\'s Pokédex|Noibat, the Sound Wave Pokémon. Noibat can cause damage as well as create hearing problems for its opponents by emitting different sound wave frequencies.}}\n{{Animedexfooter/Pokémon|\'\'XY\'\'|Kalos}}\n\n==In the manga==\n[[File:Team Flare Noibat Adventures.png|thumb|150px|Noibat in [[Pokémon Adventures]]]]\n===In the movie adaptations===\nA Noibat appeared in the {{ma|Diancie and the Cocoon of Destruction|manga adaptation}} of \'\'[[M17|Diancie and the Cocoon of Destruction]]\'\' as a resident of [[Allearth Forest]].\n\n===In the Pokémon Adventures manga===\nIn the {{chap|X & Y}}, two {{tc|Team Flare Grunt}}s who were after {{adv|X}}\'s [[Mega Ring]] used a swarm of Noibat to attack X and his friends near the [[Super Training]] Dome.\n\n==In the TCG==\n{{main|Noibat (TCG)}}\n\n==Game data==\n===Pokédex entries===\n{{Dex/Header|type=flying|type2=dragon}}\n{{Dex/NA|gen=VI}}\n{{Dex/Gen/2|gen=VI|reg1=Kalos|num1=113|label1=Mountain|reg2=Hoenn}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=X|t=FFF|entry=They live in pitch black caves. Their enormous ears can emit ultrasonic waves of 200,000 hertz.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Y|entry=Even a robust wrestler will become dizzy and unable to stand when exposed to its 200,000-hertz ultrasonic waves.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Omega Ruby|t=FFF|entry=They live in pitch black caves. Their enormous ears can emit ultrasonic waves of 200,000 hertz.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Alpha Sapphire|t=FFF|entry=Even a robust wrestler will become dizzy and unable to stand when exposed to its 200,000-hertz ultrasonic waves.}}\n|}\n|}\n{{Dex/Gen/2|gen=VII|reg1=Alola|num1=083|label1={{gameabbrev7|USUM}}:|reg2=Kanto}}\n{{Dex/NE|[[Pokémon Sun and Moon|Sun, Moon]], [[Pokémon: Let\'s Go, Pikachu! and Let\'s Go, Eevee!|Let\'s Go, Pikachu! and Let\'s Go, Eevee!]]\u200e}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Ultra Sun|entry=Fruits are its favorite foods. This gourmet carefully picks out just the ripe ones using its sonar.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Ultra Moon|entry=It flies around in search of fruit to eat. It uses ultrasonic waves to detect which fruits are ripe.}}\n|}\n|}\n[[Category:Pokémon in the Galar Pokédex]]<!--\n{{Dex/Gen/1|gen=VIII|reg1=Galar|num1=???}}\n{{Dex/Entry2|v=Sword|v2=Shield|entry=TBD}}\n|}\n|}-->\n{{Dex/Footer}}\n\n===Game locations===\n{{Availability/Header|type=flying|type2=dragon}}\n{{Availability/NA|gen=VI}}\n{{Availability/Gen|gen=VI}}\n{{Availability/Entry2|v=