t base stat total of all {{type|Dragon}} Pokémon.\n** In addition, Noibat has the lowest base {{stat|HP}} and {{stat|Attack}} stats of any Dragon-type Pokémon, and ties with {{p|Goomy}} for having the lowest base {{stat|Defense}} among all Dragon-type Pokémon.\n* Noibat\'s German name, eF-eM, is the only Pokémon name that uses the Latin alphabet and does not start with a capital letter.\n* Originally, Noibat\'s Pokédex entry on the official Pokémon website was incorrect, showing it as a pure {{type|Flying}} Pokémon. It has been since rectified.\n* Noibat can be seen as a parallel to {{p|Zubat}}, as they are both {{type|Flying}} Pokémon based on bats and can have {{a|Infiltrator}} as a possible Ability. They also share the same base stats, with their Attack and Special Attack switched around.\n\n===Origin===\nNoibat may be based on a bat, and the design of its ears may be based on speakers.\n\n====Name origin====\nNoibat is a combination of \'\'noise\'\' and \'\'{{wp|bat}}\'\'.\n\nOnbat may be a combination of 音 \'\'on\'\' (sound), 音波 \'\'onpa\'\' (sound wave), and バット \'\'bat\'\'.\n\n==In other languages==\n{{Other languages|type=Flying|type2=Dragon\n|ja=オンバット \'\'Onbat\'\'|jameaning=From {{tt|音 \'\'on\'\'|sound}}, {{tt|音波 \'\'onpa\'\'|sound wave}}, and \'\'bat\'\'\n|fr=Sonistrelle|frmeaning=From \'\'{{tt|sonique|sonic}}\'\' and \'\'{{wp|Pipistrellus|pipistrelles}}\'\'\n|es=Noibat|esmeaning=Same as English name\n|de=eF-eM|demeaning=From \'\'{{wp|Frequency modulation|FM}}\'\'\n|it=Noibat|itmeaning=Same as English name\n|ko=음뱃 \'\'Eumbaet\'\'|komeaning=From {{tt|음 (音) \'\'eum\'\'|sound}} and \'\'bat\'\'\n|zh_cmn=嗡蝠 \'\'Wēngfú\'\'|zh_cmnmeaning=From {{tt|嗡 \'\'wēng\'\'|onomatopoeia for buzzing or humming sound}} and {{tt|蝠 \'\'fú\'\'|bat}}\n|zh_yue=嗡蝠 \'\'Yūngfūk\'\'|zh_yuemeaning=From {{tt|嗡 \'\'yūng\'\'|onomatopoeia for buzzing or humming sound}} and {{tt|蝠 \'\'fūk\'\'|bat}}\n|hi=नोईबॅट \'\'Noibat\'\'|himeaning=Transcription of English name\n|ru=Нойбат \'\'Noybat\'\'